			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Do they need/want a big PR battle everytime a change doesn't make it to the Live servers? It will take quite a while for the playerbase to adjust to this concept, as initially any major change on test can create havoc and anarchy on the various class messageboards. Dev's could wind up spending as much time justifying changes as they would designing the changes.
<br />

<br />
I happen to love the idea though, and feel that the EQ Design team should be much more open with ideas for changes and openly putting them on Test before they are 99% of the way designed and implemented. Involve more players in the process, create a feature that allows players to copy their main characters to the test server, do the initial design work publicly for maximum feedback and testing.
<br />

<br />
Its just a question of whether or not its too late in the lifecycle for EQ to make that kind of dramatic change to the testing process.<br />_________________<br />Naladini
