			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To compare and contrast a little bit, Planetside and SWG are quite open about their development processes, and for the most part, this seems to work well from a player relations standpoint (keeping in mind that both games have always been this way).
<br />

<br />
The catch is, especially with SWG, the game was released well before it was ready and the dev's have a nice long to-do list that is easy to publish and manage to. SWG and Planetside are also struggling a bit with their # of subscribers, so the dev's have to be very open about development plans to keep people playing (or coming back to the game).
<br />

<br />
On the other hand, EQLive is a much more mature game. In this forum we see a post quoted from Brenlo soliciting feedback on ideas to help improve the game. EQLive doesn't have a set in stone blueprint for design anymore, which makes it very difficult to say what they're going to be working on a month from now in terms of gameplay changes. Combine that with the current "culture" of the playerbase, and a relatively stable number of subscribers (for now) and you can see why they don't see the immediate need to make major changes to the testing process.
<br />

<br />
From my perspective, EQLive will suffer <span style="font-style: italic">some</span> when WoW and EQ2 are released, though its impossible to tell how much and for how long. That's why it would be good to get the testing processes changed <span style="font-style: italic">now</span>, so you don't risk alienating your remaining players 6 months from now if you decide to revamp the system.<br />_________________<br />Naladini
<br />
<a href="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/player.vm?characterId=103141102" target="_blank" class="postlink">Summoner</a> of 15 Seasons, Najena Server
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1002541" target="_blank" class="postlink">Magician</a> of 63 Seasons, <a href="http://www.stormhammer.org/forums" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stormhammer</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
