Lol.  Definitely seems like that at times, but luckily I live in Alberta, so at least I keep a BIT more.  And provincially at least, we don't do the "tax bracket" thing.  It is a flat tax rate, but with a much higher personal exemption than other provinces.  It worked out that EVERYBODY pays less than in the graduated system.  Unfortunately, we still have the graduated system from the FEDERAL taxes.  =P
